b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48517.htm)  [Next](sbe48519.htm)\n\n* * *\n\np. 729\n\n2\\. And for the same reason all follow after.\n\nBecause speech's becoming one with mind means only conjunction with the\nlatter, not merging within it; there is also no objection to what Scripture\nsays as to all other organs that follow speech being united with mind.--Here\nterminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'speech.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 3. That mind in breath...](sbe48519.htm)\n\n"